Class Resources

  • java.lang.Object
    • Resources

  • public class Resources
extends java.lang.Object
    The Resources class This class stores a HashMap that stores all the resources used during the program, to save loading time during the game.

    Course Information:

    ICS4U0 with Krasteva, V.

    Total Time Spent: 0.5 hours

    Version:
    6 06.09.2019 
     Version History:
 May 20:
 Vansh created the class, as well as all the implementation including the global static HashMap resources as well as the static add and get methods. -- 0.5 hours
    Author:
    Maria Yampolsky and Vansh Juneja

    • Method Detail

      • add

        public static void add(java.lang.String name,
                       java.lang.Object obj)
        This method is used to add Objects to the static resources Hashmap with a String identifier, to be retrieved later on.
        Parameters:
        name - The String identifier for the resource Object.
        obj - The resource Object to load and store in the resources HashMap.

      • get

        public static java.lang.Object get(java.lang.String name)
        This method is used to retrieve an Object added to the Hashmap during loading with its String identifier.
        Parameters:
        name - The String identifier of a corresponding resource Object.
        Returns:
        The corresponding resource Object from the private resources HashMap.
